On Zoilus, who had been a slave, and now wore a huge knight's ring.

Zoile, quid tota gemmam praecingere libra Te iuvat et miserum perdere Sardonycha?

1. tota-libra] To encirvle it with a whole pound weight of gold, viz. in the Setting. Compare the ‘levis anulus' of v. 61. 5, and the ‘ aes- tivum aurum' of Juvenal, i. 28.
